-- 1. [Problem Restatement] Find the unique integer n with 0 ≤ n < 101 such that 123456 ≡ n (mod 101). 2. [Key Idea] Exploit 100 ≡ –1 (mod 101), so every even power of 10 reduces to ±1 and every odd power to ±10, turning the long decimal 123456 into a short arithmetic sum. 3. [Proof] Write 123456 in base-10: 123456 = 1·10⁵ + 2·10⁴ + 3·10³ + 4·10² + 5·10¹ + 6·10⁰. Because 100 ≡ –1 (mod 101), we have 10² ≡ –1, 10³ ≡ –10, 10⁴ ≡ 1, 10⁵ ≡ 10 (all mod 101). Substituting: n ≡ 1·10 + 2·1 + 3·(–10) + 4·(–1) + 5·10 + 6 = 10 + 2 – 30 – 4 + 50 + 6 = 34 (mod 101). Since 0 ≤ 34 < 101, the required n is 34. 4. [Conclusion] The residue of 123456 modulo 101 is n = 34.
